Title: Why can't Gen Z get a job?
description:
Starting your first job can feel like stepping into the unknown. In this episode, we sit down with Saugat, Founder & Director at TEO Tribes, who has worked with top companies like Airtel, OYO, and Leverage Edu. He shares real-world advice to help freshers navigate their careers with confidence.  

We kick things off by tackling a big question, why does sales have such a bad reputation? Saugat breaks the myths and explains why understanding sales is important in any career. If you're about to start your first job, he shares practical tips on how to settle in, make a strong impression, and grow quickly.  

Before joining a company, do you really research it properly? Many don’t, and that can be a huge mistake. We discuss why researching an organization matters and how it can shape your future. We also get into the importance of professionalism, the little things that can make a big difference in how you're perceived at work.  

Thinking about freelancing instead of a corporate job? We weigh the pros and cons so you can make an informed decision. And of course, no career conversation is complete without talking about communication skills, why they matter and how to improve them to boost your career.  

💬 Got questions? Drop them in the comments!

Title: Get 55+ Marks Easily in GATE CS 2026 using this strategy
description:
Are you preparing for GATE CS and aiming to score 55+ marks? 🚀 Follow these proven strategies to ace the exam effortlessly:

1️⃣ Understand the Syllabus
🔍 Go through the entire syllabus and divide topics into high, medium, and low priority based on their weightage. Focus more on subjects like:

Data Structures and Algorithms
Operating Systems
DBMS
Computer Networks
Discrete Mathematics
Aptitude
2️⃣ Create a Study Plan
📅 Allocate at least 3–4 hours daily for preparation. Include time for:

Learning core concepts
Solving previous year questions
Attempting mock tests
3️⃣ Strengthen Basics
✔️ Build a strong foundation in subjects like Programming, Logic, and Mathematics. Watch GATE-specific lectures or join courses for conceptual clarity.

4️⃣ Solve Previous Year Papers
📜 Practice at least 10 years of GATE papers to understand the exam pattern, frequently asked topics, and difficulty level.

5️⃣ Focus on Accuracy
📝 Avoid negative marking by practicing error-free question solving. Work on time management by taking mock tests and analyzing performance regularly.

6️⃣ Revise Regularly
📖 Dedicate the last 30 days to revision. Use formula sheets and short notes for quick reviews.

7️⃣ Practice Aptitude
✅ Don't ignore General Aptitude, which can boost your score easily with minimal effort.

Scoring 55+ marks in GATE is achievable with a smart preparation plan, consistent effort, and regular practice. 💪 Start today and achieve your dream of securing a seat in a top IIT, NIT, or a PSU!

Title: Which Programming Language should you learn in 2025 ? | *Free Resources Inside*
description:
Start the challenge now: https://gfgcdn.com/tu/U4a/

Resources:- https://docs.google.com/document/d/1R...

Which Programming Language Should You Choose in 2025?
With new frameworks and technologies springing up every year, deciding on a programming language might feel overwhelming. However, 2025 brings a few front-runners to the spotlight:

Python remains top-tier for AI, data science, web development, and its vast ecosystem of libraries.
JavaScript/TypeScript drive the modern web forward, powering dynamic front-ends and robust back-ends (Node.js).

Go (Golang) gains traction for its concurrency features, scalability, and simplicity in building microservices and cloud applications.

Java continues to be a reliable workhorse in enterprise, Android app development, and large-scale systems.

Kotlin is a strong choice for Android development and is recognized by Google as the go-to for mobile apps.

0:00 Start
1:03 Web Dev
2:39 Game Dev
3:35 AI And ML
4:23 App Dev
5:15 Embedded System
5:50 Blockchain
6:26 DevOps

Ultimately, picking the right language depends on your target industry, the community support you need, and your personal interest. If you’re aiming for AI or data science, learning Python might boost your opportunities. Interested in high-speed or low-level applications? Rust or Go could be the future. Web dev enthusiasts can always benefit from advanced JavaScript/TypeScript skills. Whichever path you choose, mastering problem-solving skills and core concepts will keep you agile in the ever-changing tech world!

Title: The Only Cyber Security Roadmap you need for 2025 |
description:
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/cyber-s...

Cybersecurity Roadmap: 

Start your cybersecurity journey by mastering networking, operating systems (Linux/Windows), and cybersecurity basics like firewalls and encryption. Progress to learning tools like Wireshark and Nmap, scripting with Python, and studying ethical hacking techniques.
Advance with certifications like CompTIA Security+, CEH, and OSCP while gaining hands-on experience through bug bounty programs and Capture the Flag (CTF) events. Build your portfolio with real-world projects and stay updated through cybersecurity blogs and industry forums.
Career Roles: Security Analyst, Penetration Tester, SOC Analyst, Incident Responder, and Cybersecurity Consultant.

Title: Tech Hiring in 2025: Complete Career Guide by Bain & Company Director
description:
Changing careers can feel overwhelming, but what if we told you it’s not only achievable but could be the best choice you ever make? 
In this episode, we share the inspiring story of Pramil, who moved from sales to research and ultimately became a Director at Bain & Co. 🚀 Discover how he managed these transitions, the skills he gained along the way, and his tips for anyone considering a daring career change into tech or consulting.

In this podcast we discussed about
Career Growth: How to navigate career shifts and structure a successful journey like Pramil’s.

Early Career Choices: Should you prioritize job role, salary, or company name in your early years?

Sales Insights: Why working in sales can be a game-changer for your career.

Cultural Differences: Indian-origin companies vs. MNCs – what makes their cultures unique?

Research Career Roadmap: Essential skills and steps to excel in research-based roles.

Technology in Consulting: How advancements in tech are transforming the consulting industry.

Sustainability & Ethics: Why startups should focus on sustainable and ethical business practices.

Freelancing vs Full-Time Jobs: Which path is better for long-term career security and growth?

Connect with Pramil :   / pramil-govil

description:

description:
Welcome to the next video of our DSA Course, where we dive into the concept of DYNAMIC PROGRAMMING.

In this video, We'll break down how DP stores solutions to subproblems to avoid redundant calculations.

We will solve classic DP problems like Fibonacci Sequence and Longest Common Subsequence, with clear 
explanations. Learn how to recognize situations where DP can be applied to optimize your code.

Explore different DP approaches (top-down vs. bottom-up) and choose the best fit for your problem. And discover how DP is used in various coding scenarios, from bioinformatics to text editing.

description:
In this video, we're going to discuss how to create a Word Cloud in Python. Word Cloud is a data visualization technique used for representing text data in which the size of each word indicates its frequency or importance. Significant textual data points can be highlighted using a word cloud. Word clouds are widely used for analyzing data from social network websites. Here, for generating word cloud in Python, we'll use packages like wordcloud, pillow, etc. So, let's get started now.

Title: Image Resolution and PPI in Computer Graphics | GeeksforGeeks
description:
In this video, we're going to discuss Image Resolution and PPI (Pixels Per Inch) concepts in Computer Graphics. In the display screen, the number of horizontal and vertical pixels is called Resolution and the Image Resolution is specifically concerned with the total number of pixels (Height * Width of Image). Moreover, the Image Resolution is generally described in PPI (Pixels Per Inch). These two are quite important to understand to learn Computer Graphics. So, let's get started now.

Title: Tips For System Design Interview | Yogita Sharma | GeeksforGeeks
description:
You need to know that System Design Interviews are not like Coding Interviews where there are one or two definite solutions for the given problem - instead System Design Interviews are the subjective ones and there can be so many solutions for a particular problem depending on how you approach the problem, how you'll apply your knowledge to actually build a system, etc. And this is why cracking System Design interviews is not an easy-to-go task. 

But, to make things a bit easier for you, here we have an expert Yogita Sharma with us who is currently working as an SDE II at Careem (Uber) - she will tell you some most worthwhile and effective tips that will surely help you to ace in your upcoming System Design Interviews.

🚨 Episode Focus:
In this episode of our SQL series, we dive into one of the foundational concepts of database normalization: First Normal Form (1NF). Understanding 1NF is essential for creating efficient, organized databases and is a common topic in data management and design interviews. We’ll guide you through the key principles, breaking down the concept with clear examples to help you grasp it quickly and effectively. 📊

🔑 What You'll Learn:

📝 The definition and importance of First Normal Form
🔍 How to identify and apply 1NF in your database design
📐 Best practices for achieving 1NF and avoiding common pitfalls

Whether you're new to database design or looking to refine your knowledge, this episode on First Normal Form will enhance your understanding and prepare you for real-world applications and interviews. 🌟
